@george-roussos Using `echo "Die süße Hündin läuft in die Höhle des Bären, der sie zum Kaffeekränzchen eingeladen hat." | phonemize -l de` yields the following result `diː zyːsə hʏndɪn lɔøft ɪn diː høːlə dɛs bɛːrən dɛɾ ziː tsʊm kafeːkɾɛntsçən aɪnɡəlɑːdən hat` which seems fine to me. I also printed out the phoneme conversion while it was caching the initial run and they all seemed fine.

@thorstenMueller @repodiac Pretty sure your cleaner isn't the root cause of the problem, since I get the same results with the default cleaner. I'll try some more experiments and report back.

PS: The character based multi-speaker model is training just fine.
